==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanitary
<hw>San"i*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sanitas</ets> health: cf. F. <ets>sanitaire</ets>. See
<er>Sanity</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to health; designed to
secure or preserve health; relating to the preservation or restoration
of health; hygienic; <as>as, <ex>sanitary</ex> regulations</as>. See the
Note under <er>Sanatory</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sanitary Commission</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Commission</er>.</cd></cs> <-- sanitary napkin, an absorbant pad
worn to absorb the menstrual flow of women. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanitation</ent>⟦br⟧
